<前言><![CDATA[]]></前言>
<法規內容>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 1</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The Regulations are prescribed according to Paragraph 5 of Article 14 of Human Trafficking Prevention Act.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 2</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The competent authority referred to in the Regulations shall be the Ministry of Labor.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 3</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[ROC nationals, foreign nationals, stateless persons, individuals from the Mainland area and residents of Macau or Hong Kong with no household registration in the Taiwan area,  who are determined by a judicial police agency（unit）to be victims of human trafficking（hereinafter victims）and issued with a residence permit, valid for one year, by the Ministry of the Interior or receive a  more favorable residence permit, on the basis of residence related regulations contained in other laws, can in accordance with these regulations apply to the competent authority for a work permit and engage in work in the Taiwan area.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 4</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[When a victim applies for a work permit he or she is required to submit the following documents：
1.Application form（s）.
2.Photocopy of a residence permit valid at the time of application.
3.Photocopies of documents that confirm the applicant has been designated a victim of human trafficking by a judicial police agency（unit）.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 5</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The competent authority will issue the victim with a work permit based on the time period covered by his or her residence permit.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 6</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[In any of the following situations an application for a work permit by a victim will be denied：
1.When the validity period of a legal residence permit has expired.
2.When a legally valid residence permit is revoked by the Ministry of the Interior.
3.When the application documents are found to contain false or invalid information.
4.When the applicant is already legally working in the Taiwan area.
5.When an application does not meet stipulated regulations and the applicant fails to provide supplementary information within a set period of time.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 7</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[In any of the following situations a victim will have his or her work permit canceled or revoked：
1.When a legally valid residence permit is revoked by the Ministry of the Interior.
2.When the application documents are found to contain false or invalid information.
3.When the applicant is already legally working in the Taiwan area.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 8</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[When the competent authority issues, cancels or revokes the work permit of a victim, the Ministry of the Interior must be informed.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 9</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[These regulations are implemented on January 1, 2024.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
</法規內容>
</法規>
